import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='x', kde=True, color='blue', label='x-coordinates')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['x'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of the x-coordinates of the points?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.countplot(x='color', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the point colors?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Point Colors')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Colors', loc='upper right', labels=data['color'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
